The paper describes the application of computational pattern recognition methods to the automated identification and size analysis of scallop larvae. This involves the use of binary invariant moments and a self-organized and unsupervised ant-like clustering algorithm based on Swarm Intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
